Hiya,

Reporting that there are contradictory instructions in the challenge "Quality Assurance and Testing with Chai - Run Functional Tests using a Headless Browser".

Link to challenge: https://learn.freecodecamp.org/information-security-and-quality-assurance/quality-assurance-and-testing-with-chai/run-functional-tests-using-a-headless-browser/

Towards the top of the exercise, the instructions ask the user to test submitting for Cristoforo Colombo:

```
test('submit "surname" : "Colombo" - write your e2e test...', function(done) {
  // fill the form...
  // then submit it pressing 'submit' button.
  //
  // in the callback...
  // assert that status is OK 200
  // assert that the text inside the element 'span#name' is 'Cristoforo'
  // assert that the text inside the element 'span#surname' is 'Colombo'
  // assert that the element(s) 'span#dates' exist and their count is 1
```

However, in the area where the user/student is supposed to add their assertions, the "inline" instructions ask the user to test against Marco Polo:

```
// assert that the text inside the element 'span#name' is 'Marco'  <== BUG: This should say, 'Cristoforo'

// assert that the text inside the element 'span#surname' is 'Polo'  <== BUG: This should say, 'Colombo'
```

Let me know if there is anything else I can do.
